    {
        "content": "<p>The difficulty here is purely mathematical (my students also struggled a lot with that one). Here is a possible solution</p>\n<div class=\"spoiler-block\"><div class=\"spoiler-header\">\n<p>Solution</p>\n</div><div class=\"spoiler-content\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n<p>example {x y : ℝ} (h1 : x + 3 = 5) (h2 : 2 * x - y * x = 0) : y = 2 := by<br>\n  calc<br>\n    y = (-1/2<em>y+1)</em>(x+3)-1/2<em>(2</em>x-y<em>x)-(-5/2</em>y+3) := by ring<br>\n    _ = (-1/2<em>y+1)</em>5-1/2<em>0-(-5/2</em>y+3) := by rw [h1, h2]<br>\n    _ = 2 := by ring<br>\n  done</p>\n</div></div>",
        "id": 515016727,
        "sender_full_name": "Riccardo Brasca",
        "timestamp": 1745920896
    },
